The Chronicle Harare Bureau
FORMER Highfield legislator Psychology Maziwisa and ex-ZBC news anchor Oscar Pambuka, who were last week jailed for 30 months for fraud, have been freed on $800 bail apiece. They were found guilty of duping Zimbabwe Power Company (ZPC) of over $12 000. Harare magistrate Mr Lazini Ncube ordered the pair’s release on condition that they surrender their passports, and report once monthly to the police. <img class="wp-image-428003 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/12/PAMBUKA-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/12/PAMBUKA.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/12/PAMBUKA-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Oscar Pambuka Following their sentencing last week, the pair’s lawyer Mr Jonathan Samukange of Venturas & Samukange Legal Practitioners, successfully applied for bail pending appeal. They are appealing against both conviction and sentence. More to follow…